curam.util.common.util

Class CodeItem

  • java.lang.Object
    • curam.util.common.util.CodeItem
  • All Implemented Interfaces:
    java.io.Serializable, java.lang.Cloneable

    public class CodeItem
extends java.lang.Object
implements java.lang.Cloneable, java.io.Serializable
    An item in a code-table. Each item has a code, a localized description, a locale (used to select the localized description), a sort order for the code item within the code-table, and an enabled flag.
    See Also:

      • CodeItem

        public CodeItem()
        Creates a new code item with the fields set to their default values. The default code and description are empty strings, the default locale is null, the default sort order is zero, and the default enabled state is true.

      • CodeItem

                int sortOrder,
                boolean enabled)
        Creates a new code item.
        Parameters:
        code - The code value.
        description - The localized description.
        locale - The locale used to localize the description.
        sortOrder - The sort order within the code-table.
        enabled - Whether or not this code is enabled.
